Ten thousand trees will be planted in Karura in two years.Samsung Electronics East Africa has partnered with the Friends of Karura Forest and the Kenya Forest Service for the initiative.On Monday, Samsung EA vice president Jung Hyun Park said, &ldquo;Taking care of the environment is a pillar of our corporate citizenship programme and we are committed to the prosperity of people and the conservation of the environment. We are also committed to taking care of the planet for future generations.&rdquo;Benches will be installed for visitors to the forest.A report by the Environment ministry shows Kenya&rsquo;s forest cover stands at 7.2 per cent.The government aims to increase the tree cover to 10 per cent by 2020.Friends of Karura chairman Karanja Njoroge thanked Samsung for its support.He said the initiative will help improve air quality.